org.retal.logiweb.dao

Interface DAO<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Entity class for which interface is implemented
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CarDAO, CargoDAO, CityDAO, CityDistanceDAO, OrderDAO, OrderRouteProgressionDAO, RoutePointDAO, UserDAO

    public interface DAO<T>
    Generic interface for basic CRUD operations. If method is not implemented properly due to some reasons, it should throw MethodUndefinedException.
    Author:
    Alexander Retivov

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(T t)
        Adds entity to database.
        Parameters:
        t - entity object to add

      • read

        T read(Object... keys)
throws IllegalArgumentException
        Reads entity from database using its primary key (composite keys are supported). If no entity found with given primary key, null is returned. It is recommended to validate keys input with validatePrimaryKeys(Class[], Object...), since they are given as Object instances.
        Parameters:
        keys - set of primary keys for identifying entity
        Returns:
        found entity object or null
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - is keys input is invalid

      • readAll

        default List<T> readAll()
                 throws MethodUndefinedException
        Reads all entities from database. This method is optional to override, but if it is called with its default implementation, an exception will be thrown.
        Returns:
        List of all entities read from database
        Throws:
        MethodUndefinedException - if default method implementation is called

      • delete

        void delete(T t)
        Deletes given entity from database.
        Parameters:
        t - entity to be deleted

      • update

        void update(T t)
        Updates entity in database with corresponding primary key to given entity.
        Parameters:
        t - given entity to update database with

      • validatePrimaryKeys

        static void validatePrimaryKeys(Class<?>[] classes,
                                Object... objects)
                         throws IllegalArgumentException
        Validates primary key input in read(Object...). If input is invalid, an exception is thrown. This method should not be overridden.
        Parameters:
        classes - - primary key classes.
        objects - - primary key.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the input is invalid

      • start

        static Session start()
        Utility method which starts session and begins transaction for that session.
        Returns:
        open Session

      • end

        static void end(Session session)
        Utility method which commits transaction (if transaction is started) for given session and closes given it.
        Parameters:
        session - open Session to close
